defaultNational Crime Recording Standards (NCRS) and National Standards for Incident Recording (NSIR) audits are undertaken regularly and reported to Chief Officers and my Office both directly and through an Executive Perfo
defaultrmance Summary. 
default&#xa0;
defaultAudit results across 2013 from Gloucestershire show that 91% of crimes that should be recorded are recorded. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThis figure however fluctuates across the different crime categories, with 96% of acquisitive crimes recorded and 88% of violent
default crimes recorded. As for the classification of crimes, Gloucestershire currently has upwards of 95% of offences categorised correctly.
default&#xa0;
default This is due in the most part to the way that the Constabulary has control of the recording of crimes within the Force Cr
defaultime Validation &amp; Evaluation Unit.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe audit process was changed early in 2013 from solely looking at thematic (one crime type at a time) to a regular overall audit.
default&#xa0;
